SIMPLE: fucoid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fucoid
<hw>Fu"coid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Fucus</ets> +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Properly,
belonging to an order of alga: (<ord>Fucoide⟦ae⟧</ord>) which are
blackish in color, and produce o⟦oum⟧spores which are not fertilized
until they have escaped from the conceptacle. The common rockweeds and
the gulfweed (<gen>Sargassum</gen>) are fucoid in character.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>In a vague sense, resembling seaweeds, or of the
nature of seaweeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fucoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fucoid
<hw>Fu"coid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant, whether
recent or fossil, which resembles a seaweed. See <er>Fucoid</er>,
<pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fucoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
